Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 186, \u00a7 14.proposition: This is a civil action brought by Plaintiff Jessica Tran against her landlord, Defendant Linda Harrison, for breach of the covenant of quiet enjoyment under Massachusetts law (Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 186, § 14).

Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 218, \u00a7 19.proposition: This Court has jurisdiction pursuant to Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 218, § 19, as the amount in controversy does not exceed $25,000.

Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 223, \u00a7 1.proposition: Venue is proper in this Court pursuant to Mass. Gen. Laws ch. 223, § 1, because the Premises at issue is located in Lowell, Massachusetts, within this Court’s jurisdiction.
